Total liabilities = 3,333,720.00 + 42,584.04 = 3,376,304.04

Step 2: Total assets at end date:
- Total Assets = 19,520,226.07

Step 3: Calculate the Debt to Asset Ratio:
\[ \text{Debt to Asset Ratio} = \frac{\text{Total Liabilities}}{\text{Total Assets}} \]

Plugging in the numbers:
\[ \frac{3,376,304.04}{19,520,226.07} \approx 0.1728 \]

Expressed as a ratio rounded to two decimal places:
0.17
